'.source.gfm':
  '{number}{element}':
    'prefix': 'lia.effect.inline'
    'body': '{${1:number}}{${2:__element__}}'
    'description': """
      Use simple inline effects to highlight specific elements within a Markdown block. Simply enclose your elements withint two subsequent braces ({}{}), whereby the first one is used to hold the number of appearence, while the will contain your text, image, video, what so ever ...
      You can tweak your effects with additional animations and styling. Animate.css is included at default.

      Examples:
        This block contains some {1}{inline __effects__} that will appear {2}{subsequently}.

        Inline effects can also contain more effects {1}{I will appear first {2}{and I as a second}}.

        With styling ++ {3}{bouncing red and delayed}<!--
              class = "animated infinite bounce"
              style = "animation-delay: 3s; color: red;"
            -->
    """
    'descriptionMoreURL': 'https://liascript.github.io/course/?https://raw.githubusercontent.com/liaScript/docs/master/README.md'
    'leftLabelHTML': '<span style="color:#ff0">ðŸŽ‡</span>'


  '{from-to}{element}':
    'prefix': 'lia.effect.inline2'
    'body': '{${1:from}-${2:to}}{${3:__element__}}'
    'description': """
      Use simple inline effects to highlight specific elements within a Markdown block. Simply enclose your elements withint two subsequent braces ({}{}), whereby the first one contains two numbers separated by (-) the first number defines the time of appearence and the second one the time of disapperance. The element contains the Markdown elements for highlighting (text, videos, images, etc.)
      You can tweak your effects with additional animations and styling. Animate.css is included at default.

      Examples:
        This block contains some {1-2}{I appear at fragment 1 and disapper at 2}.

        Nesting is allowed but has to make sense {1-3}{I will rest from 1 to 3 {4}{I will not be visible}}.

        With styling ++ {1-3}{bouncing red and delayed}<!--
              class = "animated infinite bounce"
              style = "animation-delay: 3s; color: red;"
            -->
    """

    'descriptionMoreURL': 'https://liascript.github.io/course/?https://raw.githubusercontent.com/liaScript/docs/master/README.md'
    'leftLabelHTML': '<span style="color:#ff0">ðŸŽ‡</span>'


  '{{number}}':
    'prefix': 'lia.effect.block'
    'body': '    {${1:number}}\n$2'
    'description': """
      Use block effects to let entire Markdown blocks appear or disapper. It works exactly as simple inline effects. But the number of appearence has to be put in double braces.
      The entire block can also be styled and the animation tweaked, but the required comment tag has to be be defined before the Markdown block. Animate.css is included at default.

      Examples:
                          {{1}}
        This entire block will appear with the first
        fragment. And remain till the end of this slide.

                          {{2}}
        ```js
        // this works with any markdown block
        ```

        <!-- class = "animated rollIn" -->
             {{3}}
        | Also | with  |
        |------|-------|
        | any  | table |
    """
    'descriptionMoreURL': 'https://liascript.github.io/course/?https://raw.githubusercontent.com/liaScript/docs/master/README.md'
    'leftLabelHTML': '<span style="color:#ff0">ðŸŽ†</span>'


